title: Floorseal Patio Cleaner Plus (5 Litre)
features: PROFESSIONAL STRENGTH: Patio Cleaner Plus removes algae, black spot lichen, slimes, fungi, mould, and organic stains without damaging your patio, pavers, paths & driveways. This super strong patio cleaner totally rejuvenates natural stone & pavers to an as new condition. This includes surfaces like concrete, porcelain, clay-based tiles, bricks, and block pavers.
GREAT COVERAGE: A 5 litre container will cover a huge 40m2 of surface area when diluted 1:1 with clean water. This product will achieve even greater coverage rates on exterior porcelains.

EASY TO APPLY: Our Patio Cleaner Plus is easy to apply and can be used on vertical or horizontal surfaces. Simply apply with a sprayer or watering can. Pre-soak the surface with clean water before applying the cleaning fluid. Keep the product wet during the treatment time and agitate periodically. Rinse thoroughly after use. Check the dwell time required by carrying out a test patch typically 15 minutes. You can use a dwell time of over 1 hour on surfaces contaminated surfaces.

GREAT FOR: Natural stone, like sandstone, York stone, slate and more. It is also suitable for artificial surfaces like porcelain, concrete, concrete block-paving & cement-based tiles. We recommend sealing your freshly cleaned surface with one of our Floorseal sealing products to inhibit organic growth and water & oil-based staining.
BIODEGRADABLE: Patio Cleaner Plus is 100% biodegradable. Once dry the surface is safe for children, pets, and wildlife.
FURTHER DETAILS at the foot of the page.
description: Product description Floorseal Patio Cleaner Plus What are the benefits? This is no ordinary patio cleaner! This super strong patio cleaner will totally remove ingrained dirt & organic contaminations. It will totally rejuvenate your patio, pavers, paths, and driveways to an as new condition. Totally removes black spot lichen, moulds, slime, fungi, dirt & grime. 5 litres of cleaning fluid covers a huge 40m2 of surface area (diluted at 1:1) What Materials Can I Use This On? This product is safe for use on natural stone, like Indian sandstone, York stone, slate, limestone, terracotta, and all other forms of sandstone. It is also suitable for artificial surfaces like concrete, cement-based tiles, porcelain & all forms of block paving. How Do I apply? Pre-soak the surface to ensure the product is applied to wet stone. Apply the product using a simple pump-up sprayer or watering can. Do not allow the product to dry whilst it is working - continue to wet as needed. Agitate and allow to dwell from 15 minutes to over 1 hour (if required) Rinse thoroughly and allow to dry. We recommend testing this product on a small area first and applying in cool conditions. For really heavy contaminations of black spot, try our Floorseal Black Spot Remover Plus, also available on Amazon.
